[Romania's concerns about LSD risk are underlined by its position as a cattle exporting country, in particular for slaughter. The cattle population of Romania (2013 figures, OIE) are nearly 2.6 million.

Earlier information on the LSD-preventive measures planned/undertaken by Romania is included in 20160426.4184847. It will be interesting to note if Romania considers the establishment of a cordon sanitaire of vaccinated animals along its southern and southwestern borders with (LSD-infected) Bulgaria and Serbia. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4305647,122.]
